WEBVTT

00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:25.000
I'M THE PRODUCER/DIRECTOR
OF GLOBAL CITIES,

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.000
AN INTERNATIONAL
TELEVISION SERIES

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:30.000
WHICH DOCUMENTS
THE IMPACT OF IMMIGRATION

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:32.000
ON THE GLOBALIZATION PROCESS.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
HERE IN THE U.S.,
IN 1960, ONLY ONE-EIGHTH

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:39.000
OF THE POPULATION INCREASE
WAS DUE TO IMMIGRATION--

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:43.000
IN 2001, OVER ONE-THIRD OF IT.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:45.000
WHETHER BECAUSE
 OF THE PLIGHT OF REFUGEES,

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:47.000
THE NEED
 FOR CHEAP FOREIGN LABOR,

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:49.000
OR THE VERY NATURE
 OF ITS IMMIGRATION POLICY,

00:00:49.000 --> 00:00:52.000
THE U.S.
 IS FACING DEMOGRAPHIC PROBLEMS

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:53.000
THAT MAKE FOR VOLATILE,

00:00:53.000 --> 00:00:56.000
DANGEROUS
 NEW POLITICAL DISPUTES.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:57.000
TO EXAMINE THE ISSUES

00:00:57.000 --> 00:00:59.000
SURROUNDING
THE IMMIGRATION DEBATE,

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:02.000
I'VE COME TO NEW YORK CITY,
WHICH IS THE GATEWAY

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:06.000
TO THE UNITED STATES, AS FAR AS
IMMIGRATION IS CONCERNED.

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:08.000
YOU WILL HEAR
FROM ETHNIC LEADERS,

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:11.000
POLITICIANS,
AND IMMIGRATION EXPERTS.

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:15.000
LET'S BEGIN WITH FORMER
NEW JERSEY U.S. SENATOR,

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:16.000
BILL BRADLEY.

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
THE UNTOLD STORY OF AMERICA
IS THAT SINCE 1965,

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
WE'VE HAD
A NEW WAVE OF IMMIGRANTS

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:27.000
THAT HAVE ENRICHED
THE DIVERSITY OF OUR COUNTRY,

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:31.000
JUST AS
PREVIOUS WAVES HAVE DONE,

00:01:31.000 --> 00:01:33.000
AND THEY CAME FOR MANY REASONS.

00:01:33.000 --> 00:01:36.000
SOME OF THEM DID COME
TO GO TO WORK FOR COMPANIES,

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:38.000
SOME OF 'EM CAME
BECAUSE THEY FLED OPPRESSION.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:41.000
SOME OF 'EM CAME
BECAUSE THEY WANTED

00:01:41.000 --> 00:01:42.000
THE EXPERIENCE OF THE CULTURE.

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:44.000
SOME OF 'EM CAME
BECAUSE THEY WANTED

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:47.000
TO HAVE A BETTER LIFE
FOR THEIR CHILDREN.

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:50.000
WELL, MOST IMMIGRANTS
TO THE UNITED STATES

00:01:50.000 --> 00:01:54.000
ARE ADMITTED AS IMMIGRANTS,
NOT ON THE BASIS

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:57.000
OF A NEED FOR LABOR,
OR A NEED FOR SKILLS,

00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:00.000
BUT RATHER SIMPLY BECAUSE
THEY HAVE FAMILY CONNECTIONS

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
TO U.S. CITIZENS
OR LEGAL PERMANENT RESIDENTS,

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:06.000
FORMER IMMIGRANTS
TO THE UNITED STATES.

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:10.000
THERE'S NO NUMERICAL LIMIT
ON SUCH ADMISSIONS

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:13.000
FOR IMMEDIATE FAMILY
OF U.S. CITIZENS.

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:16.000
SO AS NATURALIZATION
TAKES PLACE,

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:19.000
NEWLY,
NEWLY NATURALIZED CITIZENS

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:22.000
PETITION FOR THE ADMISSION
OF THEIR FAMILY MEMBERS,

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:24.000
AND YOU GET FLOWS THAT HAVE

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:27.000
NOTHING TO DO
WITH LABOR, OR NEED FOR LABOR.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:30.000
THE CONCERN THAT MANY PEOPLE
HAVE, AND ONE THAT I HAVE,

00:02:30.000 --> 00:02:33.000
IS THE LARGE NUMBER
OF ILLEGAL IMMIGRANTS.

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:40.000
AS I TOLD YOU EARLIER,
WE HAVE OVER HALF A MILLION

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
ILLEGAL IMMIGRANTS IN THE
METROPOLITAN NEW YORK CITY AREA.

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
AND THAT, TO ME, IS WRONG,
IT SHOULD NOT BE,

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
BECAUSE WHAT YOU HAVE IS PEOPLE
WHO ARE FOLLOWING THE RULES,

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:54.000
COMING IN, AND DOING
THE THINGS THAT ARE REQUIRED,

00:02:55.000 --> 00:02:57.000
AND OTHERS
WHO'RE JUST VIOLATING THE LAW,

00:02:57.000 --> 00:03:00.000
AND COMING IN, BEING SMUGGLED
IN, HOWEVER THEY GET HERE,

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:03.000
WITH VISAS THAT ARE FORGED,
AND ALL KINDS OF THINGS.

00:03:03.000 --> 00:03:07.000
DEBATE OVER IMMIGRATION ISSUES
IN THE DEVELOPED WORLD

00:03:07.000 --> 00:03:11.000
ARE CREATING EXPLOSIVE POLITICAL
CRISES IN MANY COUNTRIES.

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:14.000
HERE IN THE U.S., 
 HUGE NEW WAVES OF IMMIGRANTS

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:17.000
CONSIDERED TOO SPICY
 FOR THE AMERICAN MELTING POT

00:03:17.000 --> 00:03:19.000
ARE ALTERING
 ITS SOCIAL TEXTURE,

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:21.000
AND CHANGING
 THE FACE OF AMERICA.

00:03:22.000 --> 00:03:25.000
MS. McHUGH, I'VE BEEN TOLD
 BY MANY NEW YORKERS

00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:27.000
THAT THE NEW WAVE
OF IMMIGRANTS,

00:03:27.000 --> 00:03:30.000
PEOPLE WHO ARRIVE
IN THE '80s AND '90s,

00:03:30.000 --> 00:03:34.000
ARE REALLY CHANGING
 THE FACE OF NEW YORK CITY.

00:03:34.000 --> 00:03:35.000
DO YOU THINK THIS IS TRUE?

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:38.000
WELL, ABSOLUTELY.
I THINK YOU CAN'T BE

00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:41.000
TWO-THIRDS OF THE CITY
AND NOT HAVE CHANGED THE--

00:03:41.000 --> 00:03:42.000
YOU KNOW, CHANGED EVERYTHING,

00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:45.000
FROM, OBVIOUSLY,
THE COMPLEXION OF THE CITY,

00:03:45.000 --> 00:03:50.000
RIGHT ON DOWN TO ITS, YOU KNOW,
ITS BASE OF BUSINESSES AND JOBS,

00:03:50.000 --> 00:03:53.000
ITS CULTURE,
ITS EDUCATION INSTITUTIONS.

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:54.000
SO, CERTAINLY I THINK

00:03:54.000 --> 00:03:57.000
THAT THIS IS
FUNDAMENTALLY CHANGING NEW YORK,

00:03:57.000 --> 00:03:59.000
AND IN WAYS
THAT MOST NEW YORKERS EMBRACE

00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:02.000
AND BELIEVE HAVE REALLY
BREATHED NEW LIFE INTO THE CITY.

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:05.000
YOU KNOW, IF YOU LOOK
AROUND THE UNITED STATES,

00:04:05.000 --> 00:04:09.000
THERE ARE A LOT OF CITIES
THAT ARE REALLY ON THE DECLINE,

00:04:09.000 --> 00:04:12.000
AND ARE TRYING TO FIGURE OUT
HOW TO GET MORE IMMIGRANTS.

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:14.000
YEAH, I MEAN, IF YOU LOOK

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:16.000
AT A LOT OF
URBAN CENTERS IN AMERICA,

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:21.000
THAT 20 YEARS AGO
WERE THOUGHT TO BE DEAD,

00:04:21.000 --> 00:04:25.000
THEY'RE ALIVE, AND THEY'RE ALIVE
BECAUSE OF IMMIGRANTS.

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:27.000
AND IF YOU LOOK AT THE CITIES
WHERE THERE HAVE BEEN

00:04:27.000 --> 00:04:31.000
FEW IMMIGRANTS,
THEY'VE MOVED VERY LITTLE.

00:04:31.000 --> 00:04:33.000
IF YOU LOOK AT THE CITIES
WHERE THERE HAVE BEEN

00:04:33.000 --> 00:04:36.000
A LOT OF IMMIGRANTS,
YOU HAVE WHOLE NEW SUBCULTURES,

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:39.000
THAT ADD TO THE DYNAMISM
AND ECONOMIC ACTIVITY,

00:04:39.000 --> 00:04:42.000
AND ULTIMATE PROSPERITY,
OF THAT COMMUNITY.

00:04:42.000 --> 00:04:44.000
RUIZ: MS. DESAI,
 THERE SEEMS TO BE

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:47.000
A LOT OF INTERACTION AMONG
 THE DIFFERENT ETHNIC GROUPS

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:51.000
THAT OCCUPY WHAT I CALL
THE CULTURAL MIDDLE GROUND

00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:54.000
HERE IN NEW YORK CITY.

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:58.000
ARE THESE GROUPS CREATING
THEIR OWN CULTURAL SPACE?

00:04:58.000 --> 00:05:01.000
THEY DO.
THEY DO CREATE THEIR OWN SPACE.

00:05:01.000 --> 00:05:04.000
THEY DO, YOU KNOW,
COME TOGETHER.

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
YOU'LL FIND POCKETS OF PEOPLE
LIVING, YOU KNOW,

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:10.000
ALMOST LIKE
IN ISOLATION AT TIMES.

00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:12.000
BUT IT'S LIKE
9:00 TO 5:00, YOU KNOW.

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:15.000
WHEN THEY ARE 9:00 TO 5:00
AT WORK, THEY ARE AMERICAN.

00:05:15.000 --> 00:05:17.000
BUT WHEN THEY GO HOME,
IT'S LIKE, GOING HOME

00:05:17.000 --> 00:05:19.000
AND EATING
YOUR OWN TRADITIONAL FOOD,

00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:23.000
AND HAVING YOUR OWN CIRCLE
OF FRIENDS FROM BACK HOME,

00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:27.000
AND YOU SPEND YOUR WEEKENDS
AT THE RELIGIOUS INSTITUTIONS.

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:31.000
BUT YOU ALSO LEARN
TO, YOU KNOW, ACCULTURATE,

00:05:31.000 --> 00:05:34.000
IS PROBABLY THE WORD,
AND LEARN TO BE AMERICAN

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:36.000
DURING THE HOURS
THAT YOU NEED TO BE AMERICAN,

00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:40.000
AND OPERATE VERY PRODUCTIVELY,

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:43.000
BUT AT THE SAME TIME MAINTAIN
 YOUR IDENTITY AND YOUR CULTURE.

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:46.000
MR. LIU, IS IT POSSIBLE
IN NEW YORK CITY

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:48.000
TO BE BILINGUAL AND BICULTURAL?

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:53.000
ABSOLUTELY, AND I WOULD THINK
THAT AS WE GET FURTHER ALONG,

00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:56.000
INTO THE FUTURE, PEOPLE
WOULD BECOME, FURTHERMORE,

00:05:56.000 --> 00:05:59.000
MULTILINGUAL, AND MULTICULTURAL.

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:02.000
YOU LOOK AT THE--
I AM ASIAN-AMERICAN,

00:06:03.000 --> 00:06:05.000
I HAVE ALWAYS BEEN
ASIAN-AMERICAN,

00:06:05.000 --> 00:06:06.000
AND I'M PROUD TO BE.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:11.000
I HAVE RETAINED MANY ASPECTS
OF MY ASIAN CULTURE,

00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:16.000
AND I AM FULLY IMMERSED
IN AMERICAN POP CULTURE.

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:19.000
SO I'M VERY FORTUNATE
TO HAVE THAT.

00:06:19.000 --> 00:06:23.000
I THINK AS, AS OUR SCHOOLS
BECOME MUCH MORE INTEGRATED,

00:06:23.000 --> 00:06:27.000
AND AS
OUR RESIDENTIAL AREAS,

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:29.000
BASICALLY THE FABRIC
OF NEW YORK CITY,

00:06:29.000 --> 00:06:33.000
BECOMES MUCH MORE INTEGRATED,
PEOPLE WILL BECOME,

00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:37.000
WHETHER THEY LIKE IT OR NOT,
MULTILINGUAL AND MULTICULTURAL.

00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:41.000
RUIZ: TO SOME AMERICANS,
 IMMIGRANTS ARE A THREATENING,

00:06:41.000 --> 00:06:44.000
RATHER THAN INVIGORATING,
 FORCE IN NATIONAL LIFE,

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:46.000
A DRAIN IN NATIONAL RESOURCES,

00:06:46.000 --> 00:06:49.000
OR EVEN A FIFTH COLUMN
 WITHIN THE NATION.

00:06:49.000 --> 00:06:51.000
AND FOR AMERICAN NATIONALISTS,

00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:55.000
IMMIGRANTS WHO REFUSE TO FULLY
INTEGRATE ARE SEEN AS A THREAT

00:06:55.000 --> 00:06:59.000
TO THE NATIONAL AND ETHNIC
IDENTITY OF THE UNITED STATES.

00:06:59.000 --> 00:07:02.000
SENATOR PADAVAN,
 NEW YORKERS TELL ME

00:07:02.000 --> 00:07:05.000
THAT MANY NEW IMMIGRANTS
ARE NOT INTEGRATING

00:07:05.000 --> 00:07:07.000
INTO THE AMERICAN WAY OF LIFE,

00:07:07.000 --> 00:07:09.000
THAT THEY'RE NOT
 BECOMING AMERICAN,

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:13.000
AND THAT THEY'RE CLINGING ONTO
THEIR OWN CULTURE AND LANGUAGE.

00:07:14.000 --> 00:07:15.000
IS THIS A CONCERN
IN NEW YORK CITY?

00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:17.000
WELL, IT'S ALWAYS A CONCERN,

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:19.000
I THINK IT'S A CONCERN
ANYWHERE IN THE WORLD,

00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:21.000
WHETHER THEY CAME
TO NEW YORK CITY,

00:07:21.000 --> 00:07:23.000
OR THEY CAME
INTO SOME EUROPEAN CITY,

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:25.000
THAT THEY BRING THEIR CULTURE,
AND THEIR RELIGION,

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:28.000
AND THEIR BACKGROUND,
AND THEIR WAY OF LIFE,

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:32.000
WITH THEM, IT'S ONLY NATURAL.

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:35.000
YOU JUST CAN'T-- BECAUSE
SOMEONE COMES ACROSS THE BORDER,

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:38.000
AND GETS OFF A PLANE AT
LA GUARDIA OR KENNEDY AIRPORT,

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:42.000
DOESN'T MEAN, ALL OF A SUDDEN,
HE IS SOMETHIN' ELSE.

00:07:42.000 --> 00:07:45.000
HE IS WHAT HE IS,
AND HE GRAVITATES TO COMMUNITIES

00:07:45.000 --> 00:07:47.000
WHERE HE FEELS
COMFORTABLE WITH OTHER PEOPLE

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:48.000
WITH SIMILAR BACKGROUNDS.

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:51.000
THE EDUCATIONAL SYSTEM
OF THE UNITED STATES

00:07:51.000 --> 00:07:54.000
HAS VERY, VERY LITTLE INPUT

00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:59.000
THROUGHOUT A CHILD'S
EDUCATIONAL YEARS

00:07:59.000 --> 00:08:03.000
REGARDING ASIAN CULTURE,
ASIAN HISTORY, ASIAN LANGUAGES.

00:08:03.000 --> 00:08:05.000
AND AS A RESULT OF THIS,

00:08:05.000 --> 00:08:08.000
IT IS MORE
A FEAR OF THE UNKNOWN.

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:10.000
AND REALLY,
THERE IS NOTHING TO FEAR,

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:15.000
BECAUSE THE ASIANS
ARE HERE IN AMERICA

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:18.000
VOLUNTARILY BY CHOICE.

00:08:18.000 --> 00:08:21.000
SOMEWHERE,
IN THEIR CURRENT GENERATION,

00:08:21.000 --> 00:08:23.000
OR THEIR MOST
PREVIOUS GENERATION,

00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:26.000
THEY'VE VOTED WITH THEIR FEET
TO COME TO AMERICA.

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:33.000
SO OUR EXISTENCE IN AMERICA
IS VERY, VERY PRECIOUS TO US.

00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:36.000
AND, THEREFORE,
WE HAVE EVERY REASON

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:39.000
TO CONTRIBUTE
TO THE SUCCESS OF THIS COUNTRY.

00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:41.000
WE BRING IT
IN MANY, MANY DIFFERENT WAYS,

00:08:41.000 --> 00:08:44.000
SOMETIMES ACADEMICALLY,
SOMETIMES IN A TECHNOLOGY,

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:47.000
SOMETIMES EVEN WITH OUR FOOD.

00:08:47.000 --> 00:08:50.000
RUIZ: WE OFTEN HEAR
 THAT ONE OF THE BASIC CONCEPTS

00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:53.000
OF AMERICAN DEMOCRACY
 IS FREEDOM OF RELIGION.

00:08:53.000 --> 00:08:54.000
DO YOU THINK THERE IS
 FREEDOM OF RELIGION

00:08:55.000 --> 00:08:57.000
FOR MINORITIES,
 HERE IN THE U.S.?

00:08:57.000 --> 00:08:58.000
THERE IS FREEDOM OF RELIGION

00:08:58.000 --> 00:09:00.000
FROM THE GOVERNMENT
POINT OF VIEW.

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:02.000
IN OTHER WORDS,
THE GOVERNMENT DOES NOT--

00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:06.000
IT GIVES YOU
THE SAME BENEFITS, SO TO SAY,

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:08.000
WHETHER YOU ARE A HINDU

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:10.000
OR AT A CHRISTIAN CHURCH,
OR WHATEVER.

00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:12.000
BUT IF YOU WERE TO ASK ME
WHETHER OR NOT

00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:16.000
THEY ARE KEPT AT THE SAME LEVEL,
THE ANSWER IS NO.

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:19.000
IN THIS SENSE, WOULD CHRISTIANS

00:09:19.000 --> 00:09:23.000
ALSO LOOK UPON THE MINORITY
RELIGIONS IN THE SAME FASHION,

00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:26.000
AS THEY PROFESS
TO HAVE THE FREEDOM OF RELIGION?

00:09:26.000 --> 00:09:28.000
PROBABLY NOT SO,

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:31.000
BECAUSE OF THE MAJORITY
OF THE CHRISTIANS.

00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:34.000
BUT FROM THE GOVERNMENTAL LEVEL,
SEEKING THE BENEFITS--

00:09:34.000 --> 00:09:36.000
FOR EXAMPLE, 
LET'S SAY WE NEED TAX EXEMPTION,

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:39.000
BECAUSE WE ARE
ALSO A RELIGIOUS ORGANIZATION.

00:09:39.000 --> 00:09:41.000
THERE IS NO DIFFERENCE.

00:09:41.000 --> 00:09:42.000
AS LONG AS
YOU ARE AN ESTABLISHED,

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:44.000
RELIGIOUS ORGANIZATION,

00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:48.000
YOU ARE ALLOWED TO GET
THE SAME KIND OF BENEFITS,

00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:50.000
WHATEVER THE GOVERNMENT ALLOWS,
WHETHER YOU ARE A CHURCH,

00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:52.000
A TEMPLE, SYNAGOGUE,
WHATEVER IT BE.

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:54.000
RUIZ:
 SENATOR PADAVAN, I SENSE

00:09:54.000 --> 00:09:56.000
THAT MANY
 NATIVE-BORN NEW YORKERS

00:09:56.000 --> 00:09:58.000
DON'T FEEL COMFORTABLE
WITH THE ARRIVAL

00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:02.000
OF HUNDREDS OF THOUSANDS
OF NON-EUROPEAN IMMIGRANTS,

00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:06.000
WHO ARE DEMANDING TO PLAY A ROLE
IN THE LIFE OF THE CITY.

00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:10.000
WHEN THE ITALIANS AND THE IRISH
CAME IN GREAT NUMBERS,

00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:13.000
AS AN EXAMPLE,
IN THE TURN OF THE CENTURY,

00:10:13.000 --> 00:10:15.000
THERE WAS SOME--
THERE WAS RESENTMENT

00:10:15.000 --> 00:10:18.000
ON THE PART OF SOME PEOPLE

00:10:18.000 --> 00:10:23.000
WHO FELT
THAT THIS WAS NOT DESIRABLE.

00:10:23.000 --> 00:10:25.000
'COURSE, TURNED OUT
THEY WERE WRONG--

00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:26.000
IT WAS DESIRABLE,
THE NET RESULT.

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:30.000
IT'S HUMAN NATURE.
WE DON'T LIKE CHANGE.

00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:31.000
AND WHEN IT'S
SIGNIFICANT CHANGE,

00:10:31.000 --> 00:10:33.000
WE LIKE IT EVEN LESS.

00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:35.000
RUIZ: MR. MARTINEZ,
 A LOT OF LATINOS

00:10:35.000 --> 00:10:39.000
COMPLAIN OF RACISM
IN NEW YORK CITY.

