I THINK THERE IS
RACISM IN THIS SOCIETY.

00:10:49.000 --> 00:10:51.000
I THINK WE'VE DONE--
WE'VE GONE A LONG WAY

00:10:51.000 --> 00:10:54.000
IN TERMS OF IMPROVING
THE RELATIONSHIP

00:10:54.000 --> 00:10:55.000
BETWEEN
THE DIFFERENT ETHNIC GROUPS,

00:10:55.000 --> 00:10:57.000
BETWEEN WHITES
AND BLACK AND LATINOS.

00:10:57.000 --> 00:11:01.000
BUT THERE STILL EXISTS
SOME FRICTION

00:11:01.000 --> 00:11:04.000
IN TERMS OF THE WAY
WE INTERACT WITH ONE ANOTHER.

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:07.000
YOU KNOW, MR. MARTINEZ,
SOME PEOPLE ARE SAYING

00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:11.000
THAT LATINOS MAKE TOO MUCH FUSS
ABOUT BEING DISCRIMINATED.

00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:15.000
THAT IS WHAT A CITY OFFICIAL
HERE IN NEW YORK TOLD ME.

00:11:15.000 --> 00:11:17.000
DO YOU THINK THAT'S TRUE?

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:19.000
WELL, I DON'T THINK
IT'S MAKING A FUSS,

00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:22.000
IT'S MORE OF
BRINGING ATTENTION AND AWARENESS

00:11:22.000 --> 00:11:24.000
THAT WE'RE NOT GETTING
THE SAME OPPORTUNITIES

